metadata.name: SILENT
metadata.description: "THE GREAT PALACE MAID" depicts a nude oriental Turkish palace maid. painting nude images of Turkish  women was a popular aesthetic taste among the French upper classes at that time. the Turkish court lady in the painting is lying a soft cotton cushion with her back to the picture. she put her left leg on her right leg, facing out of the painting, with a Turkish turban on her head, dignified and graceful features, and a gentle and virtuous look in her eyes, which is usually the standard oriental beauty face in the impression.
